<paragraph blockId="65.[174,1380,289,604]" pageId="65" pageNumber="342">mark their underground tunnels by rubbing their hip glands. Male-male aggression is pronounced just after spring snowmelt when territories are being established. When densities are high, sex ratio for reproductive individuals may approach a single male for five females.</paragraph>
